      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my bathroom sink is dripping constantly and i cant stop it. it's one of those old ones where you turn the handle to tighten it. what do i need to fix it and how do i do it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You likely need an O-ring (or a new glug valve gasket) to replace the worn-out sealing ring on your valve stem. To fix this, turn off the faucet handle, lift and remove the existing handle by popping out or unscrewing the set screw, then replace the old O-ring with a new one before reinstalling everything. Since mentions of turning a 'handle' to fix an old faucet typically implies a compression faucet, this should stop the leaks instantly, though I should verify if that's the correct mechanism based on the user's description to ensure accuracy.",
