      "content": "Do not buy a random pack; precision washers for compression faucets are usually sold as single sets or small boxes that fit the specific diameter of your valve. You can safely remove the old washer and O-ring with pliers (your wrench should suffice) if you cover the exposed end with a cloth to avoid scratching the finish or snapping the waterline off. After removing the faulty parts, thread the new washer and O-ring into place, then reassemble the handle to complete the repair.",
